SENATE RESOLUTION 100
By Oliver
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Sancia Trotter on her
selection as a Support Employee of the Year
with Metro Nashville Public Schools.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should pause to specially recognize those outstanding
school employees who have devoted their careers to providing the highest quality education for
Tennessee's students; and
WHEREAS, Sancia Trotter is one such estimable school employee, who has
distinguished herself as a professional of the greatest dedication, ability, and integrity; and
WHEREAS, a paraprofessional at Ida B. Wells Elementary School, Ms. Trotter was
recently named a Support Employee of the Year by Metro Nashville Public Schools, a most
befitting honor that recognizes the positive influence she has on so many young lives; and
WHEREAS, Sancia Trotter is an extremely talented and compassionate professional
who works assiduously to motivate her students to reach their full potential, both as scholars
and as citizens; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Trotter serves as an inspiration to her colleagues and students alike,
and her friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are fortunate to know her; and
WHEREAS, Sancia Trotter truly epitomizes the dedicated professional who is wholly
committed to the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and she should be
specially recognized; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we hereby honor and
congratulate Sancia Trotter on being named a Support Employee of the Year by Metro Nashville
Public Schools, commend her exceptional service to the children of Tennessee, salute her
professional expertise and personal excellence, and wish her all the best in her future
endeavors.
